data.name: p5finishContact.Text
data.value: You can now start using BCUninstaller. If you have any questions or would like to suggest a new feature visit the link below.

data.name: p5finishHomepage.Text
data.value: You can read detailed change logs and check out more of my software on the homepage.

data.name: p4netDesc.Text
data.value: BCUninstaller can attempt to connect to the internet for the following reasons:

data.name: p4netDesc4.Text
data.value: ● To fetch and upload application ratings

data.name: p4netErrors.Text
data.value: Every time an error occurs you will be asked if you want to send it. You can check what data is being sent in error and usage reports by inspecting their respective XML files in BCUninstaller's directory. The sent data is not shared with any third parties.

data.name: checkBoxUpdateSearch.Text
data.value: Automatically look for updates on application start

data.name: p4netUpdateAdd.Text
data.value: You can search for updates manually from the menu bar.

data.name: p4netUsageAdd.Text
data.value: Sending these statistics will help improve BCUninstaller.

data.name: pCorDesc.Text
data.value: Over time you may find that some applications will refuse to uninstall, or will just disappear from most of the uninstall managers.

data.name: pCorViewInvalid.Text
data.value: In some cases uninstallers can get corrupted, making them impossible to uninstall. BCUninstaller can remove these entries easily using the "Uninstall manually" option.

data.name: pCorViewinvalidComment.Text
data.value: Invalid uninstallers are marked in grey.

data.name: pCorOrphansMessage.Text
data.value: Sometimes whole applications can be left on your drive even after being uninstalled. This can also happen if only the uninstaller is removed.

data.name: checkBoxOrphans.Text
data.value: Show unregistered applications in the list

data.name: pCorOrphansComment.Text
data.value: Unregistered applications are marked in red. If the original uninstaller isn't found you will have to use the "Uninstall manually" option to remove them.

data.name: p3advDesc.Text
data.value: While BCUninstaller can be used as a basic uninstaller, most of its functions are aimed at power users. Proceed with caution!

data.name: p3advSyscomp.Text
data.value: Applications marked as "system components" are hidden from most of the basic uninstall managers. This tag does NOT mean that the application is a part of the operating system.

data.name: p3advProtect.Text
data.value: Protected items are marked with the "NoRemove" tag, which means that the publisher doesn't want you to remove them. This tag is often used by large software packages to prevent you from uninstalling their individual parts.

data.name: checkBoxDiisableProtection.Text
data.value: Disable protection of uninstallers marked as "protected"

data.name: p3advProtectAdd.Text
data.value: This will let you uninstall protected items.

data.name: p2viewDetail.Text
data.value: All of the uninstallers found in your system are in the main list view. Here are some ways to browse this data:

data.name: p2viewDetail1.Text
data.value: ● Use filters and search for keywords (in all columns)

data.name: p2viewDetail2.Text
data.value: ● Sort uninstallers by any column. Freely rearrange columns.

data.name: p2viewCerts.Text
data.value: Uninstallers can be signed with certificates issued by relevant authorities. If the certificate passes validation the software package has not been altered and is reputable.

data.name: p2viewAdd.Text
data.value: Verified uninstallers are marked in green, unverified are in blue. Warning: Verification can take a long time.

data.name: p1welcomeSubheading.Text
data.value: This wizard will give you a quick tour and help configure the application.

data.name: p1languageDesc.Text
data.value: You can force BCUninstaller to use a specific localization if the default language is incorrect. A restart will be performed to apply the new language.

data.name: p1languageExtradetails.Text
data.value: If you are willing to help translate BCUninstaller to your language, click on the link below to contact me. All help is greatly appreciated!
